MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Greene Street (also State Hwy 110) within the town Silverton, turn southeast onto 14th St and proceed to second bridge.

Traveling on Hwy 550 north descending down the last switch back and hill towards Silverton, take the first right off of 550 onto dirt road about 1/4 mile before 550 and State Hwy 110 split and just before the 550 Hwy Br over Mineral Creek--proceed about 1/10 mile to gauge on Mineral Cr look to your left.

From C-470 and Wadsworth. Take Wadsworth (C-121) South past Chatfield State Park. Turn left on Waterton Canyon Rd and go past Kassler Water Treatment plant.  Site is on West side of Bridge going over South Platte just past treatment plant.

MonitoringLocationName: N Fk Gunnison - At Hwy 92  Br
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From state hwy 92 within the town of Hotchkiss, turn south on B Street and proceed approx 1/2 mi to bridge.
From city of Boulder, go north 4.6 mi on US Hwy 36 to Left Hand Canyon Rd; turn west and continue 5.2 miles to James Cr/Left Hand Cr confluence.  Sample James Cr east of bridge, just before mouth.
Traveling north on Greene St (also State Hwy 110) in Silverton turn left at the San Juan County Historical Society Museum (end of town just about), sample upstream of bridge.

As you come into town (driving from Delta South to North), turn right on S.E Independence Avenue (right after gas station).  The high school is located at the end of this avenue.  You will cross Surface Creek en route.  The easiest way to get to the station will be a left turn (North) on Stonebrook Drive.  Travel approx 0.25 miles until you reach Sandstone Ct (east side of street) which is undeveloped and right next to the high school.  The station will be located directly West of Sandstone Ct. (through the trees to the creek).  There is a green drain pipe that crosses the path next to the creek.

MonitoringLocationName: Dallas Cr - CR 24 Blw Pleasant V Cr
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Ridgeway, W on HWY 62, turn R on CR 24 (Loghill), N on CR 24 at T go left, turn left at next intersection stay on CR24, go S pass a barn on right, stop at Bridge beyond, sample upstream (W) side.  This CR24 crossing is #2 of 4 and below Pleasant Valley Cr

MonitoringLocationName: La Plata - Abv Long Hollow Cr
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Travel S on Hwy 140 from Durango off Hwy 160 some 20 mi, S on Hwy 141 another 15 mi, when Cr crosses Hwy sample W of hwy

From Hwy 62 & 550 in Ridgeway, travel 8.1 mi N on 550 to the Pa Co Chu Puk Ridgeway St Pk entrance. Turn left, follow rd to Loop G campgrd, Park at N end, walk N to picnic shelter, turn left to trail NW to river, walk to river, turn right Cow Cr and go upstream 30 yds to where not braided, sample

From the junction of HWY 160/550 in Durango, travel north on 550 (Main Avenue) to 15th St.  Turn right, then left at the rail road tracks.  Continue through Rotary Park to pedestrian bridge over the Animas River.

From the junction of 160/550 in Durango, travel north on 550 (Main Avenue) to 32nd St.  Turn Right onto 32nd St.  Proceed across the bridge and turn Left onto River Bend Rd.  Sample upstream of the bridge.
Travel North on HWY 550 to Silverton, take the first right off of 550 just before the 550/110 split and town (dirt road).  Travel about five tenths of a mile up and sample.

Travel north on HWY 550 towards Ouray.  Turn right off of 550 onto Ouray CR 20D--Ironton Park.  Follow the dirt road along the river for about three tenths of a mile to the inlet circle part of the road.

Travel north on HWY 550 to Ouray.  Turn left on 7th Avenue and then right on Ouray CR 17.  Proceed down CR 17 to the USGS Gauge (there is a pedestrian bridge right by it and you can see HWY 550 from the site). Station is to your right, on Uncompahgre River.

Travel south on HWY 550/160 to the La Plata County Humane Society on the right side of the road right after  crossing the 550/160 bridge and where HWY 3 splits off to the left.  Drive down the dirt road to the river.
3.7 miles south of the light Hwy 550 at Ridgeway, is turnoff for Potter's Ranch. Turn west off of Hwy 550 onto CR 3A and travel about 1/2 mile to bridge.  Sample upstream side of bridge.

16.5 miles north of Ouray on Hwy 550. Turn at Paco Chu Puck State Pk below Ridgeway Reservoir. Travel on One way park rd to first left or sign saying picnic/walk area (continuing straight takes you to restrooms), follow road down past fish cleaning station to walking bridge (only one).  Sometimes gates are open and you can drive closer than other times.
Fr Hwy 36 (28th St) in Boulder, turn E on Arapahoe Rd and then S on 30th St.  Turn rt into Scott Carpenter Park.  Walk to cr -- site is bet the ped br and the bike path underpass.

MonitoringLocationName: Short Draw - Abv Conf N Fk Gunnison
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Bridge St in Hotchkiss, turn S on 3rd and just before street ends there is a walking path to fairgrounds on E side.  Sampling site is where path crosses Short Draw - from bridge or just downstream.
Take Hwy 586 S from Howardsville and site is located just below the gauge which is below confluence of Cunningham Cr, and a little below the cabin built on the edge of the avalanch zone from Brendel

From the junction of US Hwys 50 & 550 in the town of Montrose, take 550 southeast to Colorado Ave (across from S 9th St).  Turn right, then left at Rio Grande Ave, right at Apollo.  Follow Apollo to River Bottom Park, station is at footbridge in park.

MonitoringLocationName: Left Hand Cr - Lefthand Cr at Peak to Peak
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From the jct of Hwy 72 and Lefthand Canyon Dr in Ward, travel south 1.04 miles on Hwy 72 (MM43).  Site on creek just upstream from Hwy72, between old stone bridge and a culvert running under hwy.

MonitoringLocationName: Left Hand Cr - Lefthand Cr at California G
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Ward, travel 1.3 miles south on Lefthand Canyon Dr to the jct with California Gulch Rd and Sawmill Rd.  Next, go 0.3 mile NW on California Gulch Rd.  Site is on creek immediately west of the road.

MonitoringLocationName: Little James Cr - Above Yellow Girl
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Jamestown, take James Canyon Drive 0.5 miles. Sample location on right, marked with flags.

MonitoringLocationName: Government Draw - Abv Long Hollow Res
Long Hollow Cr - Abv Long Hollow Res
Left Hand Cr - Above James Cr
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From city of Boulder, go north 4.6 mi on US Hwy 36 to Left Hand Canyon Rd; turn west and follow Left Hand Canyon Rd 5.8 miles to a point where road crosses Left Hand Cr (0.6 mi upstream from James Cr/Left Hand Cr confluence).
From city of Boulder, go north 3.3 mi on US Hwy 36 to county Rd 26.  Turn right and follow 26 approx 1.3 mi to 41st St.  Make the mandatory left turn and proceed to first bridge.
From Jamestown take James Canyon Drive north 1.3 miles. There's a large pulloff on right. Sample site is marked with flags.
Station 672 is on a bridge over Lefthand Creek at Sue Schauffler's house at 7943 Lefthand Canyon Drive, Jamestown, CO, 80455
From junction of US Hwy 6/50 & state hwy 340, travel approx 2/3 mi west on 340 (Grand Ave) to bridge over Colorado River.

MonitoringLocationName: Long Hollow Cr - Abv Conf La Plata
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Travel S on Hwy 140 from Durango off Hwy 160 some 20 mi, S on Hwy 141 another 15 mi, when Cr crosses Hwy sample W of hwy

From town of Hermosa, travel 3.3 mi north on US Hwy 550 to CR 250 South.  Turn right and proceed 0.4 mi to bridge over Animas River.  Station is on private property just downstream from bridge OR is collected from the Br.
From town of Trimble, travel approx 2/3 mi east on county Rd 252 to bridge over Animas River.
Travel S on Hwy 140 from Durango off Hwy 160 some 20 mi, S on Hwy 141 another 15 mi, when Cr crosses Hwy sample W of hwy

From the junction of Hwy 550/160 in Durango, go north on 550 (Main Ave) until the railroad tracks cross the road.  Turn left at the light between the old powerplant and the RiverFront Building and the Bridge Cafe. Proceed down to the river and sample downstream of the the hanging bridge.

MonitoringLocationName: Junction Cr - At Colorado Trail Head
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From the intersection of 25th St and Camino Del Rio, drive W on 25th St, which will turn into Junction Cr Rd/CR204.  Proceed on this road to the Colorado Trail trailhead.  Park and walk up trail approx 0.4 miles. Cross over Sites Ditch and walk approx 25 yds past where the ditch comes off of Junction Cr.  Sample by large boulder, topped with cairns, on left side of trail.

From junction of US Hwys 160 & 550 southeast of the town Durango, travel approx 5.2 mi south on 550 to CR 213.  Turn right and follow 213 until the road turns to dirt. Continue another 3 miles or so to the split of CR 213 and 214,  curve east and that is Weaselskin Br, sample upstream. This is Ute Land so be respectful.

Take Hwy 550 N toward Silverton, W on CR 576 at Hermosa, travel up the road to private property permission required, at FS boundary at lower end of outstanding water section- site moved 200 yards downstream, From the start of La Plata County Road 202 at the intersection of County Road 203, take county road 202 for 0.7 miles to a private bridge on the left. Park and sample here with permission from private land owners of the bridge. Grab samples can be taken from the bank or bucket samples from the bridge- May 2019, private property, permission granted by owners
